450struct yy_buffer_state
451 {
452 FILE *yy_input_file;
453
454 char *yy_ch_buf; /* input buffer */
455 char *yy_buf_pos; /* current position in input buffer */

467 /* Whether we "own" the buffer - i.e., we know we created it,
468 * and can realloc() it to grow it, and should free() it to
469 * delete it.
470 */
471 int yy_is_our_buffer;
472
473 /* Whether this is an "interactive" input source; if so, and
474 * if we're using stdio for input, then we want to use getc()
475 * instead of fread(), to make sure we stop fetching input after
476 * each newline.
477 */
478 int yy_is_interactive;
479
480 /* Whether we're considered to be at the beginning of a line.
481 * If so, '^' rules will be active on the next match, otherwise
482 * not.
483 */
484 int yy_at_bol;
485
486 int yy_bs_lineno; /**< The line count. */
487 int yy_bs_column; /**< The column count. */
488
489 /* Whether to try to fill the input buffer when we reach the
490 * end of it.
491 */
492 int yy_fill_buffer;
493
494 int yy_buffer_status;
495
496#define YY_BUFFER_NEW 0
497#define YY_BUFFER_NORMAL 1
498 /* When an EOF's been seen but there's still some text to process
499 * then we mark the buffer as YY_EOF_PENDING, to indicate that we
500 * shouldn't try reading from the input source any more. We might
501 * still have a bunch of tokens to match, though, because of
502 * possible backing-up.
503 *
504 * When we actually see the EOF, we change the status to "new"
505 * (via yyrestart()), so that the user can continue scanning by
506 * just pointing yyin at a new input file.
507 */
508#define YY_BUFFER_EOF_PENDING 2
509
510 };

1348 goto yy_find_action;
1349 }
1350 }
1351
1352 else switch ( yy_get_next_buffer( ) )
1353 {
1354 case EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE:
1355 {
1356 (yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof) = 0;
1357
1358 if ( yywrap( ) )
1359 {
1360 /* Note: because we've taken care in
1361 * yy_get_next_buffer() to have set up
1362 * yytext, we can now set up
1363 * yy_c_buf_p so that if some total
1364 * hoser (like flex itself) wants to
1365 * call the scanner after we return the
1366 * YY_NULL, it'll still work - another
1367 * YY_NULL will get returned.
1368 */
1369 (yy_c_buf_p) = (yytext_ptr) + YY_MORE_ADJ;
1370
1371 yy_act = YY_STATE_EOF(YY_START);
1372 goto do_action;
1373 }
1374
1375 else
1376 {
1377 if ( ! (yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof) )
1378 YY_NEW_FILE;
1379 }
1380 break;
1381 }
1382
1383 case EOB_ACT_CONTINUE_SCAN:
1384 (yy_c_buf_p) =
1385 (yytext_ptr) + yy_amount_of_matched_text;
1386
1387 yy_current_state = yy_get_previous_state( );
1388
1389 yy_cp = (yy_c_buf_p);
1390 yy_bp = (yytext_ptr) + YY_MORE_ADJ;
1391 goto yy_match;
1392
1393 case EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH:
1394 (yy_c_buf_p) =
1395 &YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[(yy_n_chars)];
1396
1397 yy_current_state = yy_get_previous_state( );
1398
1399 yy_cp = (yy_c_buf_p);
1400 yy_bp = (yytext_ptr) + YY_MORE_ADJ;
1401 goto yy_find_action;
1402 }
1403 break;
1404 }
1405
1406 default:
1407 YY_FATAL_ERROR(
1408 "fatal flex scanner internal error--no action found" );
1409 } /* end of action switch */
1410 } /* end of scanning one token */
1411 } /* end of user's declarations */
1412} /* end of yylex */
1413
1414/* yy_get_next_buffer - try to read in a new buffer
1415 *
1416 * Returns a code representing an action:
1417 * EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH -
1418 * EOB_ACT_CONTINUE_SCAN - continue scanning from current position
1419 * EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE - end of file
1420 */
1421static int yy_get_next_buffer (void)
1422{
1423 char *dest = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf;
1424 char *source = (yytext_ptr);
1425 yy_size_t number_to_move, i;
1426 int ret_val;
1427
1428 if ( (yy_c_buf_p) > &YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[(yy_n_chars) + 1] )
1429 YY_FATAL_ERROR(
1430 "fatal flex scanner internal error--end of buffer missed" );
1431
1432 if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_fill_buffer == 0 )
1433 { /* Don't try to fill the buffer, so this is an EOF. */
1434 if ( (yy_c_buf_p) - (yytext_ptr) - YY_MORE_ADJ == 1 )
1435 {
1436 /* We matched a single character, the EOB, so
1437 * treat this as a final EOF.
1438 */
1439 return EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE;
1440 }
1441
1442 else
1443 {
1444 /* We matched some text prior to the EOB, first
1445 * process it.
1446 */
1447 return EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH;
1448 }
1449 }
1450
1451 /* Try to read more data. */
1452
1453 /* First move last chars to start of buffer. */
1454 number_to_move = (yy_size_t) ((yy_c_buf_p) - (yytext_ptr) - 1);
1455
1456 for ( i = 0; i < number_to_move; ++i )
1457 *(dest++) = *(source++);
1458
1459 if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buffer_status == YY_BUFFER_EOF_PENDING )
1460 /* don't do the read, it's not guaranteed to return an EOF,
1461 * just force an EOF
1462 */
1463 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars = (yy_n_chars) = 0;
1464
1465 else
1466 {
1467 yy_size_t num_to_read =
1468 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size - number_to_move - 1;
1469
1470 while ( num_to_read <= 0 )
1471 { /* Not enough room in the buffer - grow it. */
1472
1473 /* just a shorter name for the current buffer */
1474 YY_BUFFER_STATE b = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE;
1475
1476 int yy_c_buf_p_offset =
1477 (int) ((yy_c_buf_p) - b->yy_ch_buf);
1478
1479 if ( b->yy_is_our_buffer )
1480 {
1481 yy_size_t new_size = b->yy_buf_size * 2;
1482
1483 if ( new_size <= 0 )
1484 b->yy_buf_size += b->yy_buf_size / 8;
1485 else
1486 b->yy_buf_size *= 2;
1487
1488 b->yy_ch_buf = (char *)
1489 /* Include room in for 2 EOB chars. */
1490 yyrealloc( (void *) b->yy_ch_buf,
1491 (yy_size_t) (b->yy_buf_size + 2) );
1492 }
1493 else
1494 /* Can't grow it, we don't own it. */
1495 b->yy_ch_buf = NULL;
1496
1497 if ( ! b->yy_ch_buf )
1498 YY_FATAL_ERROR(
1499 "fatal error - scanner input buffer overflow" );
1500
1501 (yy_c_buf_p) = &b->yy_ch_buf[yy_c_buf_p_offset];
1502
1503 num_to_read = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size -
1504 number_to_move - 1;
1505
1506 }
1507
1508 if ( num_to_read > YY_READ_BUF_SIZE )
1509 num_to_read = YY_READ_BUF_SIZE;
1510
1511 /* Read in more data. */
1512 YY_INPUT( (&YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[number_to_move]),
1513 (yy_n_chars), num_to_read );
1514
1515 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars = (yy_n_chars);
1516 }
1517
1518 if ( (yy_n_chars) == 0 )
1519 {
1520 if ( number_to_move == YY_MORE_ADJ )
1521 {
1522 ret_val = EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE;
1523 yyrestart( yyin );
1524 }
1525
1526 else
1527 {
1528 ret_val = EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH;
1529 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buffer_status =
1530 YY_BUFFER_EOF_PENDING;
1531 }
1532 }
1533
1534 else
1535 ret_val = EOB_ACT_CONTINUE_SCAN;
1536
1537 if (((yy_n_chars) + number_to_move) > YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size) {
1538 /* Extend the array by 50%, plus the number we really need. */
1539 yy_size_t new_size = (yy_n_chars) + number_to_move + ((yy_n_chars) >> 1);
1540 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf = (char *) yyrealloc(
1541 (void *) YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf, (yy_size_t) new_size );
1542 if ( ! YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf )
1543 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_get_next_buffer()" );
1544 /* "- 2" to take care of EOB's */
1545 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size = (yy_size_t) (new_size - 2);
1546 }
1547
1548 (yy_n_chars) += number_to_move;
1549 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[(yy_n_chars)] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
1550 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[(yy_n_chars) + 1] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
1551
1552 (yytext_ptr) = &YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[0];
1553
1554 return ret_val;
1555}

1557/* yy_get_previous_state - get the state just before the EOB char was reached */
1558
1559 static yy_state_type yy_get_previous_state (void)
1560{
1561 yy_state_type yy_current_state;
1562 char *yy_cp;
1563
1564 yy_current_state = (yy_start);
1565
1566 for ( yy_cp = (yytext_ptr) + YY_MORE_ADJ; yy_cp < (yy_c_buf_p); ++yy_cp )
1567 {
1568 YY_CHAR yy_c = (*yy_cp ? yy_ec[YY_SC_TO_UI(*yy_cp)] : 1);
1569 if ( yy_accept[yy_current_state] )
1570 {
1571 (yy_last_accepting_state) = yy_current_state;
1572 (yy_last_accepting_cpos) = yy_cp;
1573 }
1574 while ( yy_chk[yy_base[yy_current_state] + yy_c] != yy_current_state )
1575 {
1576 yy_current_state = (int) yy_def[yy_current_state];
1577 if ( yy_current_state >= 35 )
1578 yy_c = yy_meta[yy_c];
1579 }
1580 yy_current_state = yy_nxt[yy_base[yy_current_state] + yy_c];
1581 }
1582
1583 return yy_current_state;
1584}

1586/* yy_try_NUL_trans - try to make a transition on the NUL character
1587 *
1588 * synopsis
1589 * next_state = yy_try_NUL_trans( current_state );
1590 */
1591 static yy_state_type yy_try_NUL_trans (yy_state_type yy_current_state )
1592{
1593 int yy_is_jam;
1594 char *yy_cp = (yy_c_buf_p);
1595
1596 YY_CHAR yy_c = 1;
1597 if ( yy_accept[yy_current_state] )
1598 {
1599 (yy_last_accepting_state) = yy_current_state;
1600 (yy_last_accepting_cpos) = yy_cp;
1601 }
1602 while ( yy_chk[yy_base[yy_current_state] + yy_c] != yy_current_state )
1603 {
1604 yy_current_state = (int) yy_def[yy_current_state];
1605 if ( yy_current_state >= 35 )
1606 yy_c = yy_meta[yy_c];
1607 }
1608 yy_current_state = yy_nxt[yy_base[yy_current_state] + yy_c];
1609 yy_is_jam = (yy_current_state == 34);
1610
1611 return yy_is_jam ? 0 : yy_current_state;
1612}

1620 static int yyinput (void)

1624
1625{
1626 int c;
1627
1628 *(yy_c_buf_p) = (yy_hold_char);
1629
1630 if ( *(yy_c_buf_p) == YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR )
1631 {
1632 /* yy_c_buf_p now points to the character we want to return.
1633 * If this occurs *before* the EOB characters, then it's a
1634 * valid NUL; if not, then we've hit the end of the buffer.
1635 */
1636 if ( (yy_c_buf_p) < &YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[(yy_n_chars)] )
1637 /* This was really a NUL. */
1638 *(yy_c_buf_p) = '\0';
1639
1640 else
1641 { /* need more input */
1642 yy_size_t offset = (int) ((yy_c_buf_p) - (yytext_ptr));
1643 ++(yy_c_buf_p);
1644
1645 switch ( yy_get_next_buffer( ) )
1646 {
1647 case EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH:
1648 /* This happens because yy_g_n_b()
1649 * sees that we've accumulated a
1650 * token and flags that we need to
1651 * try matching the token before
1652 * proceeding. But for input(),
1653 * there's no matching to consider.
1654 * So convert the EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH
1655 * to EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE.
1656 */
1657
1658 /* Reset buffer status. */
1659 yyrestart( yyin );
1660
1661 /*FALLTHROUGH*/
1662
1663 case EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE:
1664 {
1665 if ( yywrap( ) )
1666 return 0;
1667
1668 if ( ! (yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof) )
1669 YY_NEW_FILE;
1670#ifdef __cplusplus
1671 return yyinput();
1672#else
1673 return input();
1674#endif
1675 }
1676
1677 case EOB_ACT_CONTINUE_SCAN:
1678 (yy_c_buf_p) = (yytext_ptr) + offset;
1679 break;
1680 }
1681 }
1682 }
1683
1684 c = *(unsigned char *) (yy_c_buf_p); /* cast for 8-bit char's */
1685 *(yy_c_buf_p) = '\0'; /* preserve yytext */
1686 (yy_hold_char) = *++(yy_c_buf_p);
1687
1688 return c;
1689}

1692/** Immediately switch to a different input stream.
1693 * @param input_file A readable stream.
1694 *
1695 * @note This function does not reset the start condition to @c INITIAL .
1696 */
1697 void yyrestart (FILE * input_file )
1698{
1699
1700 if ( ! YY_CURRENT_BUFFER ){
1701 yyensure_buffer_stack ();
1702 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE =
1703 yy_create_buffer( yyin, YY_BUF_SIZE );
1704 }
1705
1706 yy_init_buffer( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER, input_file );
1707 yy_load_buffer_state( );
1708}

1710/** Switch to a different input buffer.
1711 * @param new_buffer The new input buffer.
1712 *
1713 */
1714 void yy_switch_to_buffer (YY_BUFFER_STATE new_buffer )
1715{
1716
1717 /* TODO. We should be able to replace this entire function body
1718 * with
1719 * yypop_buffer_state();
1720 * yypush_buffer_state(new_buffer);
1721 */
1722 yyensure_buffer_stack ();
1723 if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER == new_buffer )
1724 return;
1725
1726 if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER )
1727 {
1728 /* Flush out information for old buffer. */
1729 *(yy_c_buf_p) = (yy_hold_char);
1730 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_pos = (yy_c_buf_p);
1731 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars = (yy_n_chars);
1732 }
1733
1734 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = new_buffer;
1735 yy_load_buffer_state( );
1736
1737 /* We don't actually know whether we did this switch during
1738 * EOF (yywrap()) processing, but the only time this flag
1739 * is looked at is after yywrap() is called, so it's safe
1740 * to go ahead and always set it.
1741 */
1742 (yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof) = 1;
1743}
1744
1745static void yy_load_buffer_state (void)
1746{
1747 (yy_n_chars) = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars;
1748 (yytext_ptr) = (yy_c_buf_p) = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_pos;
1749 yyin = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_input_file;
1750 (yy_hold_char) = *(yy_c_buf_p);
1751}

1753/** Allocate and initialize an input buffer state.
1754 * @param file A readable stream.
1755 * @param size The character buffer size in bytes. When in doubt, use @c YY_BUF_SIZE.
1756 *
1757 * @return the allocated buffer state.
1758 */
1759 YY_BUFFER_STATE yy_create_buffer (FILE * file, yy_size_t size )
1760{
1761 YY_BUFFER_STATE b;
1762
1763 b = (YY_BUFFER_STATE) yyalloc( sizeof( struct yy_buffer_state ) );
1764 if ( ! b )
1765 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_create_buffer()" );
1766
1767 b->yy_buf_size = size;
1768
1769 /* yy_ch_buf has to be 2 characters longer than the size given because
1770 * we need to put in 2 end-of-buffer characters.
1771 */
1772 b->yy_ch_buf = (char *) yyalloc( (yy_size_t) (b->yy_buf_size + 2) );
1773 if ( ! b->yy_ch_buf )
1774 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_create_buffer()" );
1775
1776 b->yy_is_our_buffer = 1;
1777
1778 yy_init_buffer( b, file );
1779
1780 return b;
1781}

1783/** Destroy the buffer.
1784 * @param b a buffer created with yy_create_buffer()
1785 *
1786 */
1787 void yy_delete_buffer (YY_BUFFER_STATE b )
1788{
1789
1790 if ( ! b )
1791 return;
1792
1793 if ( b == YY_CURRENT_BUFFER ) /* Not sure if we should pop here. */
1794 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = (YY_BUFFER_STATE) 0;
1795
1796 if ( b->yy_is_our_buffer )
1797 yyfree( (void *) b->yy_ch_buf );
1798
1799 yyfree( (void *) b );
1800}

1802/* Initializes or reinitializes a buffer.
1803 * This function is sometimes called more than once on the same buffer,
1804 * such as during a yyrestart() or at EOF.
1805 */
1806 static void yy_init_buffer (YY_BUFFER_STATE b, FILE * file )
1807
1808{
1809 int oerrno = errno;
1810
1811 yy_flush_buffer( b );
1812
1813 b->yy_input_file = file;
1814 b->yy_fill_buffer = 1;
1815
1816 /* If b is the current buffer, then yy_init_buffer was _probably_
1817 * called from yyrestart() or through yy_get_next_buffer.
1818 * In that case, we don't want to reset the lineno or column.
1819 */
1820 if (b != YY_CURRENT_BUFFER){
1821 b->yy_bs_lineno = 1;
1822 b->yy_bs_column = 0;
1823 }
1824
1825 b->yy_is_interactive = file ? (isatty( fileno(file) ) > 0) : 0;
1826
1827 errno = oerrno;
1828}

1830/** Discard all buffered characters. On the next scan, YY_INPUT will be called.
1831 * @param b the buffer state to be flushed, usually @c YY_CURRENT_BUFFER.
1832 *
1833 */
1834 void yy_flush_buffer (YY_BUFFER_STATE b )
1835{
1836 if ( ! b )
1837 return;
1838
1839 b->yy_n_chars = 0;
1840
1841 /* We always need two end-of-buffer characters. The first causes
1842 * a transition to the end-of-buffer state. The second causes
1843 * a jam in that state.
1844 */
1845 b->yy_ch_buf[0] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
1846 b->yy_ch_buf[1] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
1847
1848 b->yy_buf_pos = &b->yy_ch_buf[0];
1849
1850 b->yy_at_bol = 1;
1851 b->yy_buffer_status = YY_BUFFER_NEW;
1852
1853 if ( b == YY_CURRENT_BUFFER )
1854 yy_load_buffer_state( );
1855}

1857/** Pushes the new state onto the stack. The new state becomes
1858 * the current state. This function will allocate the stack
1859 * if necessary.
1860 * @param new_buffer The new state.
1861 *
1862 */
1863void yypush_buffer_state (YY_BUFFER_STATE new_buffer )
1864{
1865 if (new_buffer == NULL)
1866 return;
1867
1868 yyensure_buffer_stack();
1869
1870 /* This block is copied from yy_switch_to_buffer. */
1871 if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER )
1872 {
1873 /* Flush out information for old buffer. */
1874 *(yy_c_buf_p) = (yy_hold_char);
1875 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_pos = (yy_c_buf_p);
1876 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars = (yy_n_chars);
1877 }
1878
1879 /* Only push if top exists. Otherwise, replace top. */
1880 if (YY_CURRENT_BUFFER)
1881 (yy_buffer_stack_top)++;
1882 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = new_buffer;
1883
1884 /* copied from yy_switch_to_buffer. */
1885 yy_load_buffer_state( );
1886 (yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof) = 1;
1887}

1889/** Removes and deletes the top of the stack, if present.
1890 * The next element becomes the new top.
1891 *
1892 */
1893void yypop_buffer_state (void)
1894{
1895 if (!YY_CURRENT_BUFFER)
1896 return;
1897
1898 yy_delete_buffer(YY_CURRENT_BUFFER );
1899 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = NULL;
1900 if ((yy_buffer_stack_top) > 0)
1901 --(yy_buffer_stack_top);
1902
1903 if (YY_CURRENT_BUFFER) {
1904 yy_load_buffer_state( );
1905 (yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof) = 1;
1906 }
1907}

1909/* Allocates the stack if it does not exist.
1910 * Guarantees space for at least one push.
1911 */
1912static void yyensure_buffer_stack (void)
1913{
1914 yy_size_t num_to_alloc;
1915
1916 if (!(yy_buffer_stack)) {
1917
1918 /* First allocation is just for 2 elements, since we don't know if this
1919 * scanner will even need a stack. We use 2 instead of 1 to avoid an
1920 * immediate realloc on the next call.
1921 */
1922 num_to_alloc = 1; /* After all that talk, this was set to 1 anyways... */
1923 (yy_buffer_stack) = (struct yy_buffer_state**)yyalloc
1924 (num_to_alloc * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*)
1925 );
1926 if ( ! (yy_buffer_stack) )
1927 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yyensure_buffer_stack()" );
1928
1929 memset((yy_buffer_stack), 0, num_to_alloc * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*));
1930
1931 (yy_buffer_stack_max) = num_to_alloc;
1932 (yy_buffer_stack_top) = 0;
1933 return;
1934 }
1935
1936 if ((yy_buffer_stack_top) >= ((yy_buffer_stack_max)) - 1){
1937
1938 /* Increase the buffer to prepare for a possible push. */
1939 yy_size_t grow_size = 8 /* arbitrary grow size */;
1940
1941 num_to_alloc = (yy_buffer_stack_max) + grow_size;
1942 (yy_buffer_stack) = (struct yy_buffer_state**)yyrealloc
1943 ((yy_buffer_stack),
1944 num_to_alloc * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*)
1945 );
1946 if ( ! (yy_buffer_stack) )
1947 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yyensure_buffer_stack()" );
1948
1949 /* zero only the new slots.*/
1950 memset((yy_buffer_stack) + (yy_buffer_stack_max), 0, grow_size * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*));
1951 (yy_buffer_stack_max) = num_to_alloc;
1952 }
1953}

1955/** Setup the input buffer state to scan directly from a user-specified character buffer.
1956 * @param base the character buffer
1957 * @param size the size in bytes of the character buffer
1958 *
1959 * @return the newly allocated buffer state object.
1960 */
1961YY_BUFFER_STATE yy_scan_buffer (char * base, yy_size_t size )
1962{
1963 YY_BUFFER_STATE b;
1964
1965 if ( size < 2 ||
1966 base[size-2] != YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR ||
1967 base[size-1] != YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR )
1968 /* They forgot to leave room for the EOB's. */
1969 return NULL;
1970
1971 b = (YY_BUFFER_STATE) yyalloc( sizeof( struct yy_buffer_state ) );
1972 if ( ! b )
1973 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_scan_buffer()" );
1974
1975 b->yy_buf_size = (size - 2); /* "- 2" to take care of EOB's */
1976 b->yy_buf_pos = b->yy_ch_buf = base;
1977 b->yy_is_our_buffer = 0;
1978 b->yy_input_file = NULL;
1979 b->yy_n_chars = b->yy_buf_size;
1980 b->yy_is_interactive = 0;
1981 b->yy_at_bol = 1;
1982 b->yy_fill_buffer = 0;
1983 b->yy_buffer_status = YY_BUFFER_NEW;
1984
1985 yy_switch_to_buffer( b );
1986
1987 return b;
1988}

1990/** Setup the input buffer state to scan a string. The next call to yylex() will
1991 * scan from a @e copy of @a str.

2004/** Setup the input buffer state to scan the given bytes. The next call to yylex() will
2005 * scan from a @e copy of @a bytes.
2006 * @param yybytes the byte buffer to scan
2007 * @param _yybytes_len the number of bytes in the buffer pointed to by @a bytes.
2008 *
2009 * @return the newly allocated buffer state object.
2010 */
2011YY_BUFFER_STATE yy_scan_bytes (const char * yybytes, yy_size_t _yybytes_len )
2012{
2013 YY_BUFFER_STATE b;
2014 char *buf;
2015 yy_size_t n;
2016 yy_size_t i;
2017
2018 /* Get memory for full buffer, including space for trailing EOB's. */
2019 n = (yy_size_t) (_yybytes_len + 2);
2020 buf = (char *) yyalloc( n );
2021 if ( ! buf )
2022 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_scan_bytes()" );
2023
2024 for ( i = 0; i < _yybytes_len; ++i )
2025 buf[i] = yybytes[i];
2026
2027 buf[_yybytes_len] = buf[_yybytes_len+1] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
2028
2029 b = yy_scan_buffer( buf, n );
2030 if ( ! b )
2031 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "bad buffer in yy_scan_bytes()" );
2032
2033 /* It's okay to grow etc. this buffer, and we should throw it
2034 * away when we're done.
2035 */
2036 b->yy_is_our_buffer = 1;
2037
2038 return b;
2039}

2177int yylex_destroy (void)
2178{
2179
